## Gate C Objectives
<!-- Gate C (Backlog Readiness Review) confirms that the team is ready to begin iterative delivery. The backlog is sufficiently groomed, acceptance criteria are defined, the test plan is approved, and team capacity is confirmed. -->

Gate C validates:
- Product backlog is groomed and prioritised for at least 2 sprints ahead
- Acceptance criteria are defined for all Sprint 1 committed items
- Test plan is approved
- Team capacity is confirmed for Sprint 1
- Definition of Done is agreed by the team
- Technical environment (dev, test) is ready

